    "title":  "Inbox approval-notification i18n: subject prefix, status label, relative time",
    "description":  "## Goal\n\nLocalize the inbox notification rendering for approval items. Found during [ZAI-115](/ZAI/issues/ZAI-115) visual QA — three English strings leak through when UI language is Russian:\n\n1. **Subject prefix** — `Hire Agent: \u003cname\u003e` keeps `Hire Agent` hardcoded in English.\n2. **Approval status badge** — `Approved` is rendered as a literal English string.\n3. **Relative time** — `6h ago` is formatted in English, producing the mixed string `обновлено 6h ago`.\n\nThe wrapper word `обновлено` is already localized — the leak is in the interpolated values.\n\nVisual: see `inbox-mine-ru.png` attached to [ZAI-115](/ZAI/issues/ZAI-115). The row shows `Hire Agent: CEO` / `Approved обновлено 6h ago`.\n\n## Scope\n\nOut-of-scope from [ZAI-89](/ZAI/issues/ZAI-89), which targeted `StatusBadge` / `KeyboardShortcuts` / `SidebarAgents` / `Inbox` empty state. The approval-notification row rendering is a separate component.\n\n## Reproduction\n\n1. Run the dev server (`pnpm -C ui dev`).\n2. Open `/SDF/inbox/mine` with UI language set to Russian.\n3. Observe the approval row beneath `SDF-1`.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- Subject prefix uses an i18n key (e.g. `notifications.subjects.hire_agent`), interpolating the agent name.\n- Approval status uses an i18n status map (Approved / Rejected / Pending — at minimum, the values that can appear in inbox rows).\n- Relative time uses the locale-aware time-formatting helper already present elsewhere in the codebase (search for `formatDistanceToNow` / `formatRelativeTime` usage that already works in RU).\n- `scripts/check-i18n-only-diff.sh` clean.\n- Updated screenshot of the same row showing fully Russian text attached as proof.\n\n## Files (likely)\n\n- `ui/src/components/Inbox*.tsx` — the approval notification row.\n- `ui/src/locales/{en,ru}/notifications.json` (or `inbox.json`) — new keys for subject prefixes and status labels.\n- Time formatting helper — locate the existing relative-time formatter and ensure the inbox row uses it instead of an English-locked formatter.",
